---

## Error Handling

| Scenario | Handling |
|----------|---------|
| Docker daemon not running | `buildImage()` / `runContainer()` reject with connection error -- caller catches and marks deployment as FAILED |
| Image build fails (e.g., `RUN npm build` returns non-zero) | `buildImage()` rejects with the Docker error message from the build output |
| Container port already in use | `runContainer()` rejects with port conflict error -- caller should retry with a different port (handled by PortAllocator in Phase 5) |
| Container exits immediately after start | `waitForHealthy()` detects via `isContainerRunning()` returning `false` and returns `false` |
| `stopContainer()` called on already-stopped container | Caught gracefully -- no error thrown |
| `pruneImages()` tries to remove an image in use by a running container | `force: true` flag handles this, or catch and skip |
| `getContainerLogs()` on a container that no longer exists | Catch error and return empty string or re-throw |

---

## Verification

### client.ts

- [ ] `buildImage()` builds an image from a directory with a Dockerfile and the image appears in `docker images`
- [ ] `buildImage()` uses a custom Dockerfile path when the `dockerfile` parameter is provided
- [ ] `buildImage()` rejects when the Dockerfile has a syntax error or a build step fails
- [ ] `runContainer()` starts a container and returns a valid container ID
- [ ] `runContainer()` maps the specified host port to the container's internal port 3000
- [ ] `runContainer()` sets environment variables accessible inside the container
- [ ] `runContainer()` sets the restart policy to `on-failure` with max 3 retries
- [ ] `stopContainer()` stops a running container (SIGTERM followed by SIGKILL after timeout)
- [ ] `stopContainer()` does not throw when called on an already-stopped container
- [ ] `stopContainer()` removes the container after stopping it
- [ ] `getContainerLogs()` returns log output from a container's stdout/stderr
- [ ] `getContainerLogs()` respects the `tail` parameter
- [ ] `pruneImages()` removes old images while keeping the specified count
- [ ] `pruneImages()` only removes images matching the project name

### container.ts

- [ ] `waitForHealthy()` returns `true` when the container responds with HTTP 2xx
- [ ] `waitForHealthy()` returns `false` after exhausting all retries (10 attempts)
- [ ] `waitForHealthy()` returns `false` immediately if the container stops during health checks
- [ ] `waitForHealthy()` uses `HEALTH_CHECK.MAX_RETRIES` (10) and `HEALTH_CHECK.RETRY_INTERVAL_MS` (2000)
- [ ] `isContainerRunning()` returns `true` for running containers
- [ ] `isContainerRunning()` returns `false` for stopped/exited containers
- [ ] `isContainerRunning()` returns `false` for non-existent container IDs (no throw)
- [ ] `getContainerPort()` returns the mapped host port number
- [ ] `getContainerPort()` returns `null` if no port is mapped
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes with no errors
